SIMPLE: inclosure
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inclosure
<hw>In*clo"sure</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Inclose</er>, <er>Enclosure</er>.]</ety> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>enclosure</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of inclosing; the state of being inclosed,
shut up, or encompassed; the separation of land from common ground by a
fence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is inclosed or placed within something; a
thing contained; a space inclosed or fenced up.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Within the <qex>inclosure</qex> there was a great store of
houses.</q> <rj><qau>Hakluyt.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That which incloses; a barrier or fence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Breaking our <qex>inclosures</qex> every morn.</q> <rj><qau>W.
Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incloud</ent>⟦br⟧
